Definition: often followed by `for') ardently or excessively desirous
Example: avid for adventure; an avid ambition to succeed; fierce devouring affection; the esurient eyes of an avid curiosity; greedy for fame
Synonyms: devouring, a, esurient, greedy, often, followed, by, for, ardently, or, excessively, desirous, adventure, an, ambition, to, succeed, fierce, affection, the, eyes, of, curiosity, fame
Category: adj.all
